        "section_value": "Chief Complaint\nLeft shoulder pain.\nHistory of Present Illness\nThe patient reports pain with any movement on their left shoulder. He also reports pain in the left hand. The patient experiences pain. The patient toppled over into a weird position. The patient's pain started after toppling over. The patient was in gymnastics class. The patient was in gymnastics class. The patient did not take pain medications. The patient took tylenol.\nFindings\nExamination shows reduced active abduction of the left shoulder and pain with impingement testing.\nAssessment\nThe patient is restricted from carrying heavy weights.\nPlan\nThe doctor recommends using an ice pack to relieve pain. The doctor recommends using a heat pad to relieve pain. The patient should use their right hand instead. The doctor suggests continuing the use of ibuprofen at 600 mg three times a day for a week. The patient should come back to see the doctor if the pain is still there. The doctor recommends a follow-up in one week.",
